article.description: — Kellan Grady had 22 points as Davidson edged past UNLV 77-73 in the Maui Invitational on Wednesday night. Hyunjung Lee added 21 points for the Wildcats.
article.headline: Grady leads Davidson past UNLV 77-73
article.story: ASHEVILLE, N.C. -- — Kellan Grady had 22 points as Davidson edged past UNLV 77-73 in the Maui Invitational on Wednesday night. Hyunjung Lee added 21 points for the Wildcats. Carter Collins had 18 points for Davidson (2-2). Luka Brajkovic added 10 points. Bryce Hamilton had 27 points for the Runnin’ Rebels (0-4), whose season-opening losing streak reached four games. David Jenkins Jr. added 18 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
